{"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Instance-Properties","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ProceduralSkyMaterial\/energyMultiplier","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ProceduralSkyMaterial\/groundBottomColor","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ProceduralSkyMaterial\/groundCurve","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ProceduralSkyMaterial\/groundEnergyMultiplier","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ProceduralSkyMaterial\/groundHorizonColor","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ProceduralSkyMaterial\/skyCover","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ProceduralSkyMaterial\/skyCoverModulate","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ProceduralSkyMaterial\/skyCurve","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ProceduralSkyMaterial\/skyEnergyMultiplier","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ProceduralSkyMaterial\/skyHorizonColor","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ProceduralSkyMaterial\/skyTopColor","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ProceduralSkyMaterial\/sunAngleMax","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ProceduralSkyMaterial\/sunCurve","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ProceduralSkyMaterial\/useDebanding"],"title":"Instance Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ProceduralSkyMaterial\/godotClassName"],"generated":true,"title":"Type Properties","anchor":"Type-Properties"}],"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ProceduralSkyMaterial"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ProceduralSkyMaterial"},{"type":"text","text":" provides a way to create an effective background quickly by defining procedural parameters for the sun, the sky and the ground. The sky and ground are defined by a main color, a color at the horizon, and an easing curve to interpolate between them. Suns are described by a position in the sky, a color, and a max angle from the sun at which the easing curve ends. The max angle therefore defines the size of the sun in the sky."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ProceduralSkyMaterial","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" supports up to 4 suns, using the color, and energy, direction, and angular distance of the first four "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/DirectionalLight3D","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" nodes in the scene. This means that the suns are defined individually by the properties of their corresponding "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/DirectionalLight3D","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"s and globally by "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ProceduralSkyMaterial\/sunAngleMax","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ProceduralSkyMaterial\/sunCurve","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ProceduralSkyMaterial"},{"text":" uses a lightweight shader to draw the sky and is therefore suited for real-time updates. This makes it a great option for a sky that is simple and computationally cheap, but unrealistic. If you need a more realistic procedural option, use ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/PhysicalSkyMaterial"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ProceduralSkyMaterial"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A material that defines a simple sky for a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Sky","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" resource."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"symbolKind":"class","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot21ProceduralSkyMaterialC","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"ProceduralSkyMaterial"}],"roleHeading":"Class","title":"ProceduralSkyMaterial","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ProceduralSkyMaterial"}]},"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Material"],"title":"Inherits From","type":"inheritsFrom","kind":"relationships"},{"title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/s23CustomStringConvertibleP","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/SQ","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/SH","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/s12IdentifiableP","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VariantRepresentable","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VariantStorable"],"type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/proceduralskymaterial"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/PhysicalSkyMaterial":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/PhysicalSkyMaterial","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"PhysicalSkyMaterial","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"PhysicalSkyMaterial","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"PhysicalSkyMaterial","kind":"identif